\title{causatr: Unified Causal Effect Estimation for Methodological Triangulation}
\description{
Estimates causal effects via g-computation, inverse probability weighting, and matching for methodological triangulation. Primary engine is the parametric g-formula and iterated conditional expectation (ICE) g-computation with empirical sandwich variance estimation. Integrates WeightIt for IPW and MatchIt for matching. Supports binary, continuous, categorical, and multivariate treatments; static, dynamic, and modified treatment interventions; continuous, binary, censored, and competing-risk outcomes; survey weights and clustered data.
